name: Roslyn, WA Art Inspired Tees
description:
Roslyn,WA is surrounded by really cool places. Once the setting for the  TV show, Northern Exposure, it still has many more gems to share.

Just down the road towards the National Forest, is Wish Poosh- named for the angry beaver of local Native American legend who wanted to eat up the world before he was defeated by the coyote, Speelyi and sent to lie at the bottom of Lake Cle Elum. The Wish Poosh tee is in his grumpy honor.

Salmon LaSac is a beautiful site on the Cle Elum river named by French mountainmen after it's copious salmon.  The tee is very punny. hahahahaha...yes, I'm hilarious.

name: Animals & Plankton
description:
I am a non repentant biology nerd. I love nature and often paint it. From large mammals, all the way down to plankton. Don't even get me started on the beauty of diatoms.

more examples can be seen on the Buddy's Tail Facebook page. Ranging in price from a  small $15 ink transfer diatom on wood  to a large$350  36X48 canvas painting (see my catfish who I can't possibly part with but could do one for you).

Again, I paint on whatever I can find...whether a piece of wood washed up from the lake, cardboard from the recycling can, or sometimes if I'm feeling fancy...canvas.If you have a preference, let me know.
I am listing as $1 so it will appear as a buyable good....please message me as how to order one that you like.

name: Adapted Icons
description:
Mixed Media on reclaimed wood.

Icons from the masters.  Images from established icons or my own photographs are ink transferred onto wood, then given the Buddy's Tail treatment ( colors and techniques inspired by roadside alters and chapels of south Louisiana).

Please see Buddy's Tail Facebook page for more examples. Sizes range from 6X8 to 8X11.

name: Original Icons
description:
Icons painted on reclaimed wood. Mixed media. 
Inspired by tiny chapels and roadside altars all across south Louisiana, these are made to look like they spent a bit of time on the banks of the bayou.

Can be hung on wall or propeed on easel. Sizes range from 6X12 to 8X14.  Other sizes/images negotiable if you have a hankerin'.

name: Pet Portraits
description:
Let me paint your favorite critter- whether your pet is furry, feathered, slippery or scaled, we can bring him or her to life on canvas. 
Mixed media on 9 X 12 stretched canvas.

*Gallery wrapped canvas and/or other sizes available and negotiable upon request.

Simply mail 3-5 of your favorite pics to me (buddystail@gmail.com), so that I can get a good idea of who your pet is. If you prefer for me to compose from one pic in general, let me know, but still send the others to help me paint.

Usually takes 2-3 days to complete order and ship out.

A portion of proceeds will be donated to our wonderful local animal rescue organization, ARRF.
